    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>2 cups idly rice</li>
            <li>1 cup urad dal (black gram)</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon fenugreek seeds</li>
            <li>Salt to taste</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Wash the idly rice, urad dal, and fenugreek seeds separately and soak them in water for 4-6 hours.</li>
            <li>Grind the soaked urad dal and fenugreek seeds together to a smooth batter. Transfer to a large bowl.</li>
            <li>Grind the soaked idly rice to a slightly coarse texture. Mix it with the urad dal batter in the bowl.</li>
            <li>Add salt to the batter and mix well. Allow it to ferment overnight or for at least 8 hours.</li>
            <li>Grease the idly molds with a little oil and pour the batter into each mold.</li>
            <li>Steam the idlies for 10-15 minutes or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.</li>
            <li>Allow them to cool slightly before removing from the molds.</li>
            <li>Serve hot idlies with coconut chutney and sambar.</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

